  "text": "Neuroimaging and post-mortem studies have implicated BBB dysfunction as an early and common occurrence in AD, characterized by microbleeds, impaired glucose transport, disrupted functioning of P-glycoprotein 1, perivascular deposits of blood-derived proteins, cellular infiltration and degeneration of endothelial cells [CITATION_1] . Since the function of the BBB is to strictly regulate the blood-to-brain and brain-toblood transport of solutes, MTf may simply leak through the disrupted BBB into the general circulation, leading to diminished levels of CSF MTf in the MCI-c at baseline. As the BBB is also known to be disrupted in AD, CSF MTf will also be expected to be reduced in AD, but this was not observed.",
